 America and Europe, and then do some laboratory work. I might add that for six years I have been a Research Fellow in Entomology on the staff of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard.1





Sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: JASON EPSTEIN

CC, 2 pp.

Ithaca, N.Y.





1 October 1956

